# Keep agent rules and skills in sync

> **Source of truth:** [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) (intro). This file is **not** generated by
> `_sync_agent_rules.py` — edit it here and in `AGENTS.md` together when the workflow changes.

## When this applies

Run sync **before you finish** any task that edits:

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `AGENTS.md` | Canonical rules (§1–§6) |
| `.agents/skills/**/SKILL.md` | Canonical skills (OpenCode/ZCode via junction) |
| `Scripts/_sync_agent_rules.py` | Sync script itself |

If you touch a **generated mirror** (`.cursor/rules/study-*.mdc`, `md-to-pdf.mdc`, or
`.cursor/skills/**/SKILL.md`), do **not** hand-edit it — update the canonical source and
re-run sync instead.

## Mandatory workflow

From the repo root:

```powershell
python Scripts/_sync_agent_rules.py
python Scripts/_sync_agent_rules.py --check
```

1. **`_sync_agent_rules.py`** — writes `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` from `AGENTS.md` §1–§6 and
   copies `.agents/skills/` → `.cursor/skills/`. (`.opencode/skills/` is a junction to
   `.agents/skills/` — no separate copy.)
2. **`--check`** — exits with an error if mirrors are stale. Run after sync and before commit.

## Same commit

Include sync output in the **same commit** as the canonical edit:

- `AGENTS.md` + updated `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`
- `.agents/skills/**` + updated `.cursor/skills/**`

## Completion check

- [ ] `python Scripts/_sync_agent_rules.py` ran after the last canonical edit
- [ ] `python Scripts/_sync_agent_rules.py --check` passes
- [ ] No hand-edited drift in generated `.mdc` or `.cursor/skills/` files
